parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air suspension system can cause the vehicle to become unstable and unsafe to drive, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle rests higher on one side than the other
the headlights illuminate upwards towards the sky or downwards into the ground
the vehicle goes into air shock

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front suspension can cause uneven tire wear, affect vehicle alignment, and lead to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: Constantly worn-out front tires on the inner tread

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear suspension can cause the vehicle to become unstable and unsafe to drive, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
symptoms: rear sway bar end links failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview mirror can cause poor visibility, blind spots, and decreased night vision, which can lead to accidents or safety hazards.
symptoms: The rearview mirror is not clear
or has a spot that does not dim properly

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Slipping or Failure to Engage
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping or failure to engage can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to loss of control, accidents, or stalling, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle hesitates or jerks when shifting gears
the gear shift slides up and down intermittently
the vehicle will not move or will only move a short distance
the vehicle rolls forward or backward without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended vehicle movement can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially when the vehicle is parked or stopped.
symptoms: the vehicle rolls forward or backward without warning
the vehicle jumps out of park and moves unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rack and pinion system can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the power steering gear can cause loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the air spring system can cause uneven vehicle height, affecting steering and stability, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
The failure of the clock spring can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult to maneuver the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Failure in Wet Conditions
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system in wet conditions can cause loss of power steering assist, making it difficult to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: No power steering assist in wet conditions
